Five different damage scenarios are investigated in this study, derived from three different types of early stage damage. These include one scenario of connection degradation between the tower and floater implemented by removing two of the eight mounting bolts, two scenarios of blade cracks, and two scenarios of added mass simulating potential ice accumulation. The last four scenarios are separately implemented on a single blade, with the two blade crack scenarios (C1 and C2) being implemented last due to their irreversibility. All damage scenarios, along with their abbreviations, are depicted in Figure 3 and described in more detail below:
Connection degradation between the tower and floater designated as ‘B’;
Added Mass 1 (m = 1.7 g), designated as ‘M1’;
Added Mass 2 (m = 2.3 g), designated as ‘M2’;
Blade Crack 1 (L = 1.5 cm, 4% of the blade’s overall length), designated as ‘C1’;
Blade Crack 2 (L = 3 cm, 8% of the blade’s overall length), designated as ‘C2’.
